Petrochemicals company Astron Energy has confirmed that an incident occurred at its Milnerton refinery, in the Western Cape, in the early hours of July 2, but says the resultant fire has been contained and the plant stabilised. The company immediately activated its emergency response procedures and notified the relevant authorities when the incident occurred, it says. The company plans to provide more information about what happened on site once it has confirmed the details. News wire service Reuters quoted an unnamed source as saying that two people had been killed and many others injured in the incident. Astron has a network of about 850 Caltex branded service stations and operates the country’s third-largest crude oil refinery, with a capacity of 100 000 bbl/d.